g.title: j535996986
g.text: Sometimes I have to ask myself why you’re still here.

g.title: j3509764402
g.text: Oh Gods. Sorry. I didn't mean it like that. I'm just having trouble seeing MYSELF as the reason you'd tolerate all... this.

g.title: j4148389415
g.text: ... are we talking about the same people here?

g.title: j2862055404
g.text: I mean… we know what we’re doing now. We’re containing the spread. You’ve done what you were sent to do. You don’t HAVE to stay. And yet…

g.title: j2447623152
g.text: Oh, don't get cryptic. I'll feel compelled to worm the information out of you somehow.

g.title: j2983227304
g.text: I'm so sick of having this conversation with people. I'm not leaving. That's it. [End.]

g.title: j3511166397
g.text: I care about this team immensely. You're all... a family to me, now. One I've never really had.

g.title: j1048268204
g.text: And I thank the Gods for the day you joined us.

g.title: j104668664
g.text: I thought the fact that we were together would be a good enough hint as to why I wanted to be here.

g.title: j1373293198
g.text: Do I have to spell it out? I’m here because of you. [Confess feelings.]

g.title: j729092197
g.text: I'm glad you found what you were looking for. All rivers find their way to the sea, eventually.

g.title: j2893992434
g.text: Well, now I’m wondering what I did to trick you. Or manipulate you. Maybe I put some kind of suggestion in your head.

g.title: j3579245348
g.text: Well, now I’m wondering what I did to trick you. Or manipulate you. Maybe I put some kind of suggestion in your head. Or maybe there’s a secondary Techrot virus in your system that’s attracted to what’s in mine.

g.title: j217640282
g.text: Or maybe there’s a secondary Techrot virus in your system that’s attracted to what’s in mine.

g.title: j2503221460
g.text: I’m attracted to YOU, Eleanor. For all sorts of reasons.

g.title: j2132401550
g.text: As families go, this one's a mess. But I wouldn't change it for the world.

g.title: j367262482
g.text: Or maybe (deep breath) you actually like me the same way I like you. Could it really be that simple?

g.title: j3508940356
g.text: I’ll make a deal with you. Go and see Lettie, ask her to run you through a quick psych-eval, get to the bottom of whatever’s REALLY going on here, and we’ll just forget this conversation ever happened.

g.title: j2440560020
g.text: I thought I already made that clear.

g.title: j2484901191
g.text: I don’t need a psych-eval. There’s nothing crazy about liking you. If you don’t feel the same way about me, please say so.

g.title: j2297095924
g.text: If you don't feel the same way about me, just come out and say it.

g.title: j3473045456
g.text: OF COURSE I FEEL THE SAME WAY

g.title: j2211581195
g.text: YOU ARE THE BEST THING THAT EVER BLOODY HAPPENED IN MY ABSURD LIFE

g.title: j3578704679
g.text: WHICH MEANS YOU’RE NOT GOING TO BE PART OF IT FOR LONG AND THE SOONER WE BOTH ADMIT THAT THE BETTER

g.title: j2726829353
g.text: I know you’ve lost people. So have I. We’re not alone in that.

g.title: j2493653884
g.text: Eleanor, I’m not going anywhere. Right here, with you, is where I want to be.

g.title: j3286168369
g.text: Right. I can see you've made your mind up.

g.title: j2024005522
g.text: No. We’re not alone, are we? And we never have to be.

g.title: j4266688892
g.text: I could come up with a dozen different reasons why we shouldn’t be together, and you’d have an answer for every one of them. Oh, what if I infect you? You’re immune. What if I try to eat you? You’re functionally immortal. What if I see inside your head? I’m sure you’d just kick me out again.

g.title: j360888395
g.text: You wonderful, impossible creature. You’ve only gone and won me over, you have.

g.title: j908328709
g.text: Oh, one last thing. I don’t know if you’ve noticed, but I have this embarrassing personal problem. We do need to address it.

g.title: j3384571774
g.text: Your glowing eyes keeping me awake at night?

g.title: j1635792596
g.text: That's more embarrassing for OTHER people.

g.title: j3214532155
g.text: Well I’m not talking about the size of my arse am I?

g.title: j2578878941
g.text: No. I'm referencing my tongue. The anaconda in the room.

g.title: j682954532
g.text: Tell me, honestly. How do you feel about it?

g.title: j2332381007
g.text: Yes, the tongue. The anaconda in the room.

g.title: j542570620
g.text: It’s gross, but for you, I'll look past it.

g.title: j3511182726
g.text: It’s not a problem for me.

g.title: j2429847888
g.text: So... I'm not the first tentacle-tongued woman you've flirted with? Actually, don't answer that. I'm scared to learn the answer.

g.title: j1674316755
g.text: Oh! I see! You imagined you were doing me a favour!

g.title: j1964706508
g.text: I’m scared. Excited. Nervous. Frankly, more than a little aroused. Might be getting ahead of myself there.

g.title: j146157407
g.text: I'm afraid the closest you will get to me now is if you set yourself on fire.

g.title: j2382340282
g.text: I wish you the best of luck finding a less 'gross' person to be intimate with.

g.title: j969470762
g.text: In which event, I might bring myself to piss on you.

g.title: j2118981850
g.text: I... need some more time to think this over.

g.title: j1324221541
g.text: Of course. Let's do that, then.

g.title: j2924639915
g.text: How do you think the others are going to take it?

g.title: j1481250228
g.text: Gods. I hadn’t even thought of that.

g.title: j2127332711
g.text: Right now I’m too happy to care, but I suppose we ought to tell them.

g.title: j4050938194
g.text: Hmm. I’m thinking seriously about pouncing you in Arthur’s office and ‘accidentally’ turning the tannoy on so that Lettie can hear every gasp.

g.title: j2801067765
g.text: Better not, though. Life’s traumatic enough as it is.

g.title: j794173937
g.text: It’s a nice idea. Though maybe not the security office, and not with the tannoy on.

g.title: j160391016
g.text: It's the loudspeaker thing. 'The Mall will be closing in five minutes, blah blah blah, shoplifting is punishable by summary execution.'

g.title: j1704144326
g.text: Hold that thought, lover. Let’s see where imagination takes us.

g.title: j1525372512
g.text: So help me, I do love how bewildered you are sometimes.
